Sentencas: A novel BaCe0.4Zr0.3 Sn0.1Y0.2O3-delta (BSY) electrolyte membrane with thickness of 20 mu m was fabricated on NiO-based anode substrate via a one-step all-solid-state method followed by a co-sintering at 1450 degrees C for 5 h. Chemical stability test demonstrated that BSY electrolyte showed adequate chemical stability against CO2 and H2O at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: A novel anode supported BaCe0.4Zr0.3Sn0.1Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte membrane for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Besides, the doping of Sn also enhanced the conductivity in humidified hydrogen.
Titulo: A novel anode supported BaCe0.4Zr0.3Sn0.1Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte membrane for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With Nd0.7Sr0.3MnO3-sigma Cathode and hydrogen fuel, the fuel cell generated maximum output of 320, 185 and 105 MW cm(-2) at 700, 650 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A novel anode supported BaCe0.4Zr0.3Sn0.1Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte membrane for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The interfacial resistance of the fuel cell was studied under open circuit conditions and the short-term cell performance also confirmed the stability of BSY electrolyte membrane.
Titulo: A novel anode supported BaCe0.4Zr0.3Sn0.1Y0.2O3-δ electrolyte membrane for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells
